   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.5358_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>Skerryvore</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Bournemouth</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1885-08-24">Monday 24 August</date>
               </dateline>
               <note><handShift rend="pencil"/>[1885]</note>

               <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I expect to arrive in <placeName ref="#pl:Dorchester">Dorchester</placeName> tomorrow
               or next day; and if I shall be strong enough, I shall do myself the pleasure of
               calling on you â€“ if not, I shall let you know at what inn I put up, and perhaps you
               will be kind enough to call on me? I think you must have heard of me from <persName
                  ref="#ps:EdmundGosse">Gosse</persName>; <unclear>&amp;</unclear> from <pb n="2"
                  facs="uoedh_hl_h.5358_2.jpg"/> whom, if the time had served, I could have got an
               introduction; but my acquaintance with your mind is already of a old a date, that I
               scarce felt such formalities were needed; and if you should be busy or unwilling, the
               irregularity of my approach leaves you the safer retreat.</p>


            <closer>
               <salute>Yours truly</salute>
               <signed><hi rend="underlined">Robert Louis Stevenson</hi>.</signed>
               <salute>Thomas Hardy Esq.</salute>
            </closer>


         </div>
      </body>
